The paper proposes a logic-based method for knowledge graph completion (KGC) task, which involves learning first-order rules from knowledge graphs. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses optimizations for rule generation and evaluation, which could also relate to the sub-categories of Computation and Language (cs.CL) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
